Program: Letter from America by Alistair Cooke
Title: Racial discrimination, 1976
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03zjndn
Last Broadcast Date: Boxing Day 1976
Attorney General Griffin Bell's membership of private club with restricted membership. Racial discrimination in US clubs. This archive edition of Letter from America was recorded by one of two listeners, who between them taped and labelled over 650 Letter From America programmes from 1973 to 1989. It was restored by the BBC in 2014. Show less